create container with following config.
	- name the container "demo-app"
	- run the container in deamon mode
	- publish the port as 0.0.0.0/0:9090->80
	- use mitrasonu/demo-app as a base image
	- verify ip:9090


create container with following config
	- set container name as myDB
        - run the container in daemon
        - publish the port as 0.0.0.0/0:3307->3306
        - use mitrasonu/mariadb  as a base image
	- initialize enviornmenr variable:
		MARIADB_ROOT_PASSWORD=Pa55word
		MARIADB_DATABASE: migration
		MARIADB_USER: lisa
		MARIADB_PASSWORD: Pa55word
	  
Download Mysql Dump from https://github.com/sonulodha/docker/blob/master/01_docker/testDB.sql
Restore migration database.



Install mysql server /mariadb server in alpine linux .

